                <div class="l-content-container">
                    <h2>A city to explore</h2>
                    <div><p>Only a 10-minute walk from campus, Madison is a city that hosts some great attractions. Feel like taking a break from studying? Check out the Shakespeare Theatre of New Jersey or Mayo Performing Arts Center. Do you want to do some shopping? Take a trip to the Livingston Mall. Whatever your interests, Madison has something for everyone.</p>
</div>
                </div>
            </section>
                    <section class="l-page-block l-text-block bottom-line">
                <div class="l-content-container">
                    <h2>Nightlife in Madison</h2>
                    <div><p>Do you enjoy a night out? Madison has a number of hotspots. From bars and clubs to pool halls and live music lounges, Madison has a variety of venues that will keep you entertained. Some favorites include Shanghai Jazz Restaurant &amp; Bar and 54 Main Bar &amp; Grille.</p>
</div>
                </div>
            </section>
                    <section class="l-page-block l-text-block bottom-line">
                <div class="l-content-container">
                    <h2>New York: a hub for sports entertainment</h2>
                    <div><p>New York is home to many sporting events. A city full of major league games, there is a variety that you can choose from. Whether you prefer hockey, golf, running or sailing, you can catch a game in the city. Want to experience something unique to New York? Visit the Yankee stadium for a baseball game, catch a football game with the Giants in the fall, or watch runners bid for the best time during The NYC Marathon in the winter.</p>
</div>
                </div>
            </section>
                    <section class="l-page-block l-text-block bottom-line">
                <div class="l-content-container">
                    <h2>A full range of restaurants</h2>
                    <div><p>Many Madison restaurants are very affordable. However, if you are looking for a more upscale experience you can find plenty of options in the city. New York City offers more dining options than you could ever need. The New York City Department of Health reports there are nearly 20,000 restaurants within the five boroughs of New York City. There's always a new restaurant to try!</p>
</div>
                </div>
            </section>
                    <section class="l-page-block l-text-block bottom-line">
                <div class="l-content-container">
                    <h2>Shopping in Madison</h2>
                    <div><p>Madison is home to numerous boutique shops and clothing outlet malls. Whether you are looking to find great bargains or more high-end fashion deals, there is a place for you. Some popular destinations are the Madison Avenue shops, the Mall at Short Hills or Golden Shopping Mall, all within close driving distance.</p>
</div>
                </div>
            </section>
                    <section class="l-page-block l-text-block bottom-line">
                <div class="l-content-container">
                    <h2>Festivals and events</h2>
                    <div><p>In Madison there is always an event or festival to enjoy, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>New Jersey Winter Wine Festival – allowing you to explore the local wineries.</li>
<li>Parsippany - Troy Hills' Fall Festival – an annual event full of entertainment and attractions.</li>
<li>Union County Music Fest – showing you the best of national and local musicians.</li>
</ul>
</div>
                </div>
            </section>
                    <section class="l-page-block l-text-block bottom-line">
                <div class="l-content-container">
                    <h2>How much do things cost?</h2>
                    <div><p>Here's a quick breakdown of how much you should plan to pay for certain items in Madison:</p>
<ul>
<li>Restaurant and take-out meals: $10-$25.</li>
<li>Cup of coffee: $2-$4.</li>
<li>Cell phone plan: $60-$100 per month. A deposit may be required: $50-$300.</li>
<li>One-way bus ticket from Madison to New York City: $9.35</li>
<li>One-way train fare from Madison to New York City: $11.75</li>
</ul>
<p>Don't forget to tip! To reward good customer service, Americans tip between 15-20% in addition to the total bill price. This is optional, but common for restaurant wait staff, taxi drivers, nail and hair salons, etc.</p>
</div>
                </div>
            </section>
                    <section class="l-page-block l-text-block bottom-line">
                <div class="l-content-container">
                    <h2>Explore in and around Madison</h2>
                    <div><p>Are you curious to explore outside the city? Catch a NJ Transit bus to visit neighboring towns. If you want to make a trip to New York City, get to New York’s Penn Station or Hoboken.</p>
</div>
                </div>
            </section>
                


